<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA ADS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "Fighting Back," editorial, Aug. 14: 
</P>
<P>
 I can't believe the state of California has made ads insulting Texas, the 
state that has led the nation in creating jobs for the past three years.Sure, 
Texas may have mosquitoes, hurricanes and humidity, but that is nothing 
compared to California's earthquakes, fires and droughts. Californians should 
really be saying how good their state is instead of bashing others. 
</P>
<P>
 MOISES CANALES 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Rosa, Tex. 
