<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV RATINGS; 'HOME IMPROVEMENT' KEEPS ITS LOCK ON TOP SPOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On the day when ABC announced that "Home Improvement" would be moving from 
Wednesdays to Tuesdays this fall, the reigning No. 1 TV show in the land showed 
up in its familiar spot atop the national ratings. 
</P>
<P>
 Figures compiled by the A. C. Nielsen Co. showed that "Home Improvement," 
starring Tim Allen and Patricia Richardson, was seen in about 15.7 million 
homes last week, with "Grace Under Fire" right behind, just as it is on the 
current ABC schedule, and just as it will be when the pair moves to 9-10 p.m. 
Tuesdays next month. 
</P>
<P>
 Whether they will still finish atop the ratings is anybody's guess, but the 
odds would seem to be against them. On Wednesdays, they had no competition from 
other comedy shows; on Tuesdays, the viewer in search of laughs will be able to 
choose between them and the tandem of "Frasier" and "The John Larroquette Show" 
on NBC. 
</P>
<P>
 And "Frasier," the "Cheers" spinoff, certainly has a devoted following. It 
finished No. 3 last week. 
</P>
<P>
 Moves can be beneficial, of course. CBS reported that "The Nanny," which 
earlier had been languishing on Wednesdays, won its Monday night time slot for 
the fifth week in a row. Southland Ratings 
</P>
<P>
 Here are A.C. Nielsen's Top 10 prime-time programs in the Los Angeles area 
during the same week. Each rating point equals 50,064 households. 
04,05,27,09,08 Program Station Rating 1. Roseanne KABC 14.9 2. Seinfeld KNBC 
14.3 3. Grace Under Fire KABC 13.8 4. Murphy Brown KCBS 13.8 5. Fresh Prince of 
Bel-Air KNBC 13.7 6. Home Improvement KABC 13.6 7. The Simpsons KTTV 13.5 8. 
Frasier KNBC 12.9 * Frasier (10 p.m.) KNBC 12.9 10. Married ... With Children 
KTTV 12.9 Weekly Averages 
</P>
<P>
 ABC: 9.5 
</P>
<P>
 CBS: 9.4 
</P>
<P>
