<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROLLER HOCKEY; BULLFROGS DEFEAT BLADES IN OPENER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Yuri Krivokhija and Victor Gervais each scored two goals and the Anaheim 
Bullfrogs scored four in the fourth quarter on the way to a 9-6 victory over 
the Los Angeles Blades in a Roller Hockey International playoff game at The 
Pond of Anaheim on Tuesday before 8,310. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams play Game 2 of the Pacific Division finals tonight at 7:30 at the 
Forum.If the Bullfrogs win, they advance to the Western Conference finals. 
</P>
<P>
 If the Blades win, the teams will play a 12-minute mini-game immediately 
following the game to determine the series winner. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Wilson had two goals and two assists for the Blades, and Nick Vachon 
scored with 13.6 seconds remaining in the third quarter to tie the score, 5-5. 
</P>
<P>
 But Anaheim scored three unanswered goals in the first seven minutes of the 
fourth quarter to take control. 
</P>
<P>
 Blade goalie Max Mikhailovsky had 30 saves after being named the league's most 
valuable player and goaltender of the year Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Blade Coach Bobby Hull Jr. was named Western Conference coach of the year. 
MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
