<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISH REPORT: SUMMER WANES, BUT FUN HASN'T AT BIG BEAR LAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The high-profile activity at Big Bear Lake this weekend will be the National 
Mountain Bike Championships, but Cliff Fowler of Big Bear Sporting Goods 
advises that the fishing -- unusually good for so late in the summer -- 
shouldn't be overlooked. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's incredible," Fowler said. "You would think by the trout activity that 
they aren't looking at the calendar. Normally, we'd be singing the summer 
blues. We're still nailing 'em." 
</P>
<P>
 Highlight of the day, Fowler said, is the crowd that gathers on the docks at 
Gray's Landing on the north side for the hot evening bite. 
</P>
</TEXT>
