<P>
 At&T, Delta Sign $2.8-Billion Deal: The companies said they will set up a 
joint firm to provide computer services to tourism and transport companies as 
part of the 10-year agreement. The deal will push Delta Air Lines Inc. into the 
profitable transportation information business and give AT&T Corp. a solid edge 
in overhauling Delta's computer systems.The partnership between the 
telecommunications giant and the nation's third-largest airline will develop 
new information technology services to be used by Delta and sold to other 
travel and transportation companies. The deal excludes airline and travel 
agency computer reservations systems. The venture, which has not yet been 
named, will supply computer services to Atlanta-based Delta, which is 
overhauling its communications as part of a restructuring. 
