<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 KOCE Channel 50, Orange County's public television station, raised about 
$221,000 with its 12-day summer fund drive, topping the total from last 
summer's 10-day drive by about $42,000 and seeing an increase in the number of 
members and donors from 2,664 to 2,706. To what do station officials attribute 
this success? Four -- count 'em, four -- broadcasts of the "Encore! The Three 
Tenors," the televised concert with Jose Carreras, Placido Domingo and Luciano 
Pavarotti.The drive ended Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Works by some 80 Southern California artists will be on the block for the 
Orange County Center for Contemporary Art's fourteenth annual benefit auction, 
Sept. 18. The auction itself will begin at 7 p.m.; a party with wine and 
munchies runs from 5-9 p.m. at OCCCA, 3621 W. MacArthur Blvd., Space 111, Santa 
Ana. Works to be sold will be on view at OCCCA from Sept. 14-18, 11 a.m.-4 p.m. 
Admission to the auction and party is $15 per person or $25 per couple. 
Reservations must be made by Sept. 10. (714) 549-4989. 
</P>
