 CLEAN NEEDLES: The L. A. City Council wants to prevent police interference 
with activists who give clean needles to drug addicts (B1), but such "needle 
exchanges" have been taking place in the Valley for at least three years. . . . 
Clean Needles Now, an anti-AIDS group, estimates that it has distributed 50,000 
