<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; STORE EMPLOYEES ROBBED AT GUNPOINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police were searching Tuesday for two men who robbed employees of an Oxnard 
clothing store at gunpoint. 
</P>
<P>
 According to authorities, a man approached two Fashion Bug employees in the 
store's parking lot on Rose Avenue about 9 a.m. Monday and demanded money. 
</P>
<P>
 The two employees, who were on their way to a bank to deposit store receipts, 
told police that the man pointed a gun at one of them and demanded the bag, 
which contained $1,154, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 After grabbing the bag, the man fled to a waiting vehicle and was driven away 
by a second man with a rifle, authorities said.  
</P>
<P>
 Police later found the vehicle abandoned at Indiana Avenue in Oxnard. The 
vehicle had been reported stolen. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
