<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SERVICE UNION BACKS TALLMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The union that represents non-teaching employees of the Ventura County 
Community College District has voted to endorse a former administrator in the 
November election. 
</P>
<P>
 Members of the Service Employees International Union, Local No. 535, which 
represents about 350 college district secretaries, technicians and other 
workers, have endorsed John Tallman in his campaign for the Area 1 seat on the 
governing board. 
</P>
<P>
 Cheryl Herrmann, the Ventura College lab technician who serves as union vice 
president on the campus, said Tallman has a reputation for supporting 
classified employees within the three-campus college district. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's in favor of an employee's right to decide for an agency shop, he's 
against the privatization of public education and he supports fiscal 
accountability," Herrmann said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tallman is a former college district administrator who retired last year after 
more than 20 years of service. 
</P>
<P>
 He is challenging appointed incumbent Karen Boone and Ventura businessman Jim 
Hibbs on the Nov. 8 ballot for the Area 1 seat on the board. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
