<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN WOULD WELCOME RETURN OF HEITMANN; VOLLEYBALL: GERMAN NATIONAL TEAM MEMBER 
COULD RETURN FOR SENIOR SEASON. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The story of Oliver has taken a twist -- a good one for backers of the Cal 
State Northridge men's volleyball team. 
</P>
<P>
 Oliver Heitmann, a German National Team member who was the Matadors' top 
player last season, wants to return to Northridge for another campaign. 
</P>
<P>
 By telephone from Hamburg, Germany, Luise Heitmann, Oliver's grandmother, said 
the 6-foot-7 middle blocker "would very much like to" play his senior season at 
Northridge. Heitmann was unavailable for comment. 
</P>
<P>
 "We didn't anticipate him coming back," Matador Coach John Price said. "With 
him, I have a chance to be a pretty good coach again." 
</P>
<P>
 Heitmann, a second-team All-American, paced Northridge with 569 kills, a .445 
attacking percentage and 136 blocks. 
</P>
<P>
 Price said Heitmann would be an even stronger force in his second season with 
the Matadors, after adjusting to the differences between international play and 
top-level U.S. collegiate competition. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge has advanced to postseason competition the past five seasons 
largely because of a flow of dominant players -- including Coley Kyman, a 
three-time All-American -- in the middle. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first time in years, the Matadors face the prospect of replacing both 
middle blockers. Craig Hewitt, who played opposite Heitmann last season, has 
exhausted his eligibility. 
</P>
<P>
 Ed Bond, Eric Klootwyk and Larry Corbi are considered the front runners to 
replace Hewitt. 
</P>
<P>
 Travis Ferguson, a UC San Diego transfer, is expected to take over at setter. 
Peter Piexoto and Collin Smith are back at the swing hitter spots, and Jason 
Hughes and Jon Baer will be vying for time at opposite hitter. 
</P>
<P>
 Heitmann's last contact with Northridge coaches came more than a month ago. Of 
late, Price said, he and the player have been playing "phone tag." 
</P>
<P>
 "We need to figure out what type of class schedule he needs to have," Price 
said. "But if he wants to come back, there shouldn't be a problem." 
</P>
<P>
 Luise Heitmann said her grandson is unsure what arrangements to make and is 
waiting for instructions. 
</P>
<P>
 His coach has them. "I'll tell you what he should do," Price said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Call me. I'll take it from there." 
</P>
</TEXT>
