<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; JAZZ ARTIST TO PLAY IN LIBRARY 
COURTYARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Contemporary jazz recording artist Gregg Karukas is scheduled to perform 
Saturday night at the San Juan Capistrano Library courtyard. 
</P>
<P>
 Karukas, who has released four albums and was an original keyboardist for the 
Rippingtons, is also scheduled to be joined by guest vocalist Shelby Flint. 
</P>
<P>
 Two shows will be performed, at 7 and 9 p.m. The library is at 31495 El Camino 
Real. 
</P>
<P>
 Karukas has recorded songs with Kenny G and David Benoit. He has also worked 
with several Brazilian musicians, including Ricardo Silveira and Sergio Mendes. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 493-1752.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
