<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; NURSERY SCHOOL TO HOST SUMMER PICNIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUSS LOAR 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Irvine Community Nursery School will hold its 21st annual summer picnic at 
the school's new location at 2 Shoreline in Heritage Park, from 10 a.m. to noon 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The annual event precedes the 22nd school year of the only accredited "parent 
participation" preschool in the city, according to school officials. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's actually a parent-run school," school spokeswoman Shellie Artenian said. 
"We've been working with the city on getting this new location for about a 
year." 
</P>
<P>
 The school, which moved from 2 Stonecreek South in Woodbridge Village, has 48 
students from age 2 years and 9 months to pre-kindergarten. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited. For more information, call (714) 786-2687. RUSS LOAR 
</P>
