MOTORCYCLIST KILLED ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Van Nuys motorcyclist was killed Tuesday when he lost control of his cycle 
as he tried to brake to avoid a slow-moving car with its lights off on the San 
Diego Freeway, the California Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Glenn Lovins, 24, died shortly after midnight on the freeway just south of Bel 
Air Crest Road, said Officer Maria Ingram of the CHP's West Los Angeles office. 
</P>
<P>
 Lovins, who was driving about 50 m.p.h., "panicked and locked up his rear 
tire," Ingram said. "He didn't hit the car, but he hit the pavement," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 The motorcyclist was declared dead at the scene by the coroner's office, 
Ingram said. The investigation is continuing. 
