VOTES ON CRIME BILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the past 30 years more than 500,000 people have died from gunshot wounds; 
each year 37,000 lives are lost because of gunfire, and 150,000 individuals are 
wounded. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighborhoods are pleading for help, law enforcement officials are outgunned, 
but our legislators are listening to the National Rifle Assn. The next 
tough-on-crime speech we hear from any of the Orange County delegates who voted 
