<P>
TWO FOOTBALL PLAYERS HELD IN VEGAS SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police arrested two Fullerton College football players during practice Tuesday 
on murder warrants in connection with the slaying of a woman in Las Vegas in 
May. 
</P>
<P>
 Acting on information provided by the Las Vegas Metropolitan Police 
Department, Fullerton Detective Tom Basham, a gang investigator, went to the 
school's campus on East Chapman Avenue about 3:45 p.m. and arrested Anthony 
Steven James, 20, and Malcolm Lathion Gray, 19, both of Corona. 
</P>
<P>
 They were taken to Fullerton City Jail and later transferred to Orange County 
Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim was identified as Amy Tuttle, who was killed May 5 at the Mission 
Apartments in Las Vegas, according to Las Vegas Police Officer Dave Radcliffe. 
</P>
<P>
 Police here and in Las Vegas could provide no further details of the killing. 
</P>
<P>
 Head Coach Gene Murphy said the two players were "walk-ons," Anthony a running 
back and Gray a linebacker. They had not played in any games. 
</P>
<P>
 The murder warrants for James and Gray were issued Monday by the Clark County, 
Nev., district attorney's office, Radcliffe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The arrests were the result of a joint effort by Corona and Fullerton police, 
Radcliffe said. Nevada expects to extradite the men for trial, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Times correspondent Erik Hamilton contributed to this story. 
</P>
