<TEXT>
<P>
 A man suffered a severe electrical shock Tuesday when he touched a 
high-voltage transformer at Southern California Edison's Gisler Avenue power 
station, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, believed to be in his 40s, suffered second-degree burns over about 
70% of his body and was in critical condition at UCI Medical Center in 
