WOMAN KILLED AT HUSBAND'S GRAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An elderly woman tending the grave of her husband was shot and killed Tuesday 
when a group of bank robbers apparently saw her while changing vehicles at the 
cemetery, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruby Parker, 81, was shot near this central Texas town, about 100 miles north 
of Houston, after eight men robbed the Normangee State Bank of about $100,000. 
</P>
<P>
 A Texas state trooper was also injured in the incident when he was shot in the 
shoulder during a car chase as the bank robbers left the cemetery in two 
vehicles, the Leon County Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
 Four of the eight bank robbers were later captured. 
</P>
<P>
 The wounded officer was listed in stable condition at a local hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents of Normangee said the shooting of Parker was believed to be the 
first homicide in the town of about 600 people in the last 25 years. 
