<TEXT>
<P>
 Northwest Opening: HomeBase, the Irvine-based home improvement chain that 
recently closed some stores to boost its profitability, will open a new 
warehouse in Vancouver, Wash., this weekend, HomeBase President Allan Sherman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The new warehouse covers 105,404 square feet of space, along with a large 
nursery and a drive-through lumber yard. It will employ 110 people. 
</P>
<P>
 Sherman also said that HomeBase employees have donated $177,000 to the City of 
Hope National Medical Center and Beckman Research Institute. HomeBase is a 
member of the City of Hope Hardware-Home Improvement Industry Council. The 
medical institutions are in Duarte, about 25 miles northeast of Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
