<HEADLINE>
<P>
FURON'S PROFIT JUMPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Furon Co., an engineered polymer components company based in Laguna Niguel 
reported a 69% increase in second-quarter profit to $2.7 million, or 30 cents a 
share, from $1.6 million, or 18 cents a share, for the corresponding period 
last year. Sales for the quarter ended July 30 were up to $75.1 million from 
$70.2 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
