<TEXT>
<P>
 Clarification -- Due to erroneous information supplied to The Times, Friday's 
Morning Report contained incorrect information about the upcoming record 
release "Mickey Unrapped."The album, featuring Mickey Mouse and friends 
performing sendups of rap songs, will be released by Walt Disney Records Sept. 
21 in collaboration with Bellmark Records. The album features performances by 
Tag Team, Whoopi Goldberg and Color Me Badd. Rappers Salt-N-Pepa and Hammer do 
not perform, although versions of their songs are included. 
</P>
